    • Method Detail

      • getHCost

        public <E> int getHCost(State<E> state)
        This Heuristic adds all path travel times in desiredTrips as well as all transfer times except the two most expensive. This guarantees that the hCost will always be ≤ the true cost from state to the goal State.
        Specified by:
        getHCost in interface Heuristic
        Parameters:
        state - The current State.
        Returns:
        A guess of how far away the current State is from the goal State, the StateComparator then uses this guess to sort the State objects in a PriorityQueue by f(x) = g(x) + h(x), where:
        • f(x) an approximation of how much the path containing this State will cost
        • g(x) is the actual cost of the path taken till the current State.
        • h(x) the guess returned by Heuristic.getHCost(State).
